                <exercise>
                    <title>Problems</title>
                    <task workspace="4in">
                        <statement>
                            <p>
                           Prove that for all <m>a,b,c \in \mathbb{R}</m>, we have the following:
<ol>
  <li>
    <p>
      <m>a=b</m> if and only if <m>a+c = b+c</m>;
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>
      <m>0a=0</m>;
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>
      <m>-a = (-1)a</m>;
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>
      <m>(-1)^{2} = 1</m>;
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>
      <m>-(-a) = a</m>;
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>
      If <m>a \neq 0</m>, then <m>(a^{-1})^{-1}=a</m>;
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>
      If <m>a \neq 0</m> and <m>ab=ac</m>, then <m>b=c</m>.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>
      If <m>ab=0</m>, then either <m>a=0</m> or <m>b=0</m>.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>
                            </p>
                        </statement>
                    </task>
                    
